<header>
	
		
		Read this sample answer to the writing task in the last exercise and find the mistakes. There are 12. Click on them.
		
		
	
</header>
	
<section id="body">
  <img class="rightFloat" src="../media/WB_WR8s.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"/>
  <img class="leftFloat" src="../media/_WB_WR8.jpg" mode="16" id="1003"/>
  <div id="targetspotting">
  <p>The flow chart illustrates the process which the Hong Kong Post Office&#xA0;<g id="t1">is used</g>&#xA0;to select suitable artwork for its stamps.</p>
  <p>The first stages&#xA0;<g id="t2">are involved</g>&#xA0;gathering ideas for possible themes. District councils, tourist associations and government departments are all&#xA0;<g id="t3">invite</g>&#xA0;to send in suggestions to the Post Office. These are then forwarded to a special stamp advisory committee which&#xA0;<g id="t4">simultaneously</g>&#xA0;chooses between six and eight of the best ideas.</p>
  <p><g id="t5">Prior to this</g>, the committee may decide&#xA0;<g id="t6">or</g>&#xA0;to use the work of professional artists or to hold a competition and ask the public to enter their own artwork.&#xA0;<g id="t7">In case</g>&#xA0;professionals are to be used, three artists will normally&#xA0;<g id="t8">commissioned</g>&#xA0;to submit designs. The best of these will&#xA0;<g id="t9">choose</g>. Prior to printing, however, the design must be endorsed by the Secretary for Home Affairs. If, on the other hand, the committee decides to use amateur artwork, then a competition will be set up and publicised.&#xA0;<g id="t10">Before</g>&#xA0;entries have been submitted, the committee will&#xA0;<g id="t11">be chosen</g>&#xA0;the best and the winning artwork is&#xA0;<g id="t12">sending</g>&#xA0;for printing.</p>
  <p align="left">
    <font size="2"/>
  </p>

  </div>
</section>

<section id="fb1">
  <p align="left">
    <b>is used -&gt; </b>
    <font color="#0000ff"><b>uses</b><b>:</b>&#xA0;'the Hong Kong Post Office' is the subject of this verb in active voice.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb2">
  <p align="left">
    <b>are involved -&gt; </b>
    <font color="#0000ff"><b>involve</b><b>:</b>&#xA0;'The first stages' is the subject of this verb in active voice.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb3">
  <p align="left">
    <b>invited -&gt; </b>
    <font color="#0000ff"><b>invited</b><b>:</b>&#xA0;Passive is needed here.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb4">
  <p align="left">
    <b>simultaneously -&gt; </b>
    <font color="#0000ff"><b>subsequently</b><b>:</b>&#xA0;'simultaneously' means 'at the same time' and 'subsequently' means 'afterwards'.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb5">
  <p align="left">
    <b>Prior to this -&gt; </b>
    <font color="#0000ff"><b>At this stage</b><b>:</b>&#xA0;'Prior to this' means 'before'.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb6">
  <p align="left">
    <b>or -&gt; </b>
    <font color="#0000ff"><b>either</b><b>:</b>&#xA0;'Either' introduces the first alternative.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb7">
  <p align="left">
    <b>In case -&gt; </b>
    <font color="#0000ff"><b>If</b><b>:</b>&#xA0;'In case' does not have exactly the same meaning as 'if'.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb8">
  <p align="left">
    <b>commissioned -&gt; </b>
    <font color="#0000ff"><b>be commissioned</b><b>:</b>&#xA0;This verb is in passive voice in the future form, 'will be + past participle'. </font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb9">
  <p align="left">
    <b>choose -&gt; </b>
    <font color="#0000ff"><b>be chosen</b><b>:</b>&#xA0;This verb is in passive voice in the future form, 'will be + past participle'.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb10">
  <p align="left">
    <b>Before -&gt; </b>
    <font color="#0000ff"><b>Once</b><b>:</b>&#xA0;'Once' here means 'as soon as'.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb11">
  <p align="left">
    <b>be chosen -&gt; </b>
    <font color="#0000ff"><b>choose</b><b>:</b>&#xA0;This verb is in passive voice in the future form, 'will be + past participle'.</font>
  </p>
  <p align="left"/>
</section>

<section id="fb12">
  <p align="left">
    <b>sending -&gt; </b>
    <font color="#0000ff"><b>sent</b><b>:</b>&#xA0;The 'is' here is part of the passive verb. Present continuous is not appropriate here.</font>
  </p>
</section>

